## OpenAPI / Description Examples

### Minimal (description only)

```python
description=(
    "Get user by ID. Time: O(1) · Space: O(1)"
)
```

### With behavior and complexity

```python
description=(
    "Paginated list of orders for the current user. "
    "Time: O(page_size) · Space: O(page_size). "
    "Results ordered by created_at descending."
)
```

### When complexity is worse than target

```python
description=(
    "Legacy full-text search; no index. "
    "Time: O(n), n = total documents; prefer /v2/search for large datasets. "
    "Space: O(page_size)"
)
```

---

## Checklist (Before Merging)

- [ ] Every endpoint has **time complexity** (and space if non-trivial) in its **description**.
- [ ] Complexity matches the implementation (e.g. pagination → O(page_size), index lookup → O(1) or O(log n)).
- [ ] List/search endpoints are paginated and documented as O(page_size) (or documented reason otherwise).
- [ ] No unbounded O(n) responses; no hidden N+1 or O(n) post-processing unless documented and justified.

